<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Boldon Clocks Year's Best in Men's 100m Heats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Ato Boldon of Trinidad and Tobago ran
a fabulous fast time in the men's 100 meters second round to register
the year's fastest time of 9.87 seconds here Saturday at the 6th World
Athletics Championships.
</P>
<P>
His time is only 0.03 seconds slower than the world record set
by Donovan Bailey of Canada at the Olympics last year. The time is
also Boldon's personal best, 0.02 seconds inside his season's
leading time.
</P>
<P>
The Olympic bronze medallist had said before the race that he
could set a new world record about 9.70 seconds at the meet. With a
blistering form, he is able to do that in the final tomorrow night.
</P>
<P>
Mauice Green of the United States, whose best time this year is
9.90, equalled the time behind Boldon.
</P>
<P>
Tim Montgomery of the United States, whose best time is 9.92,
showed he is a strong force in the battle of the world fastest man,
clocked 9.99 in the following heat, ahead of Bailey's 10.10.
</P>
<P>
Bailey, who looked not in his best form, also finished second in
the morning's first round. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
