<DOCNO> XIE19970803.0005 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Taylor Sworn in as Liberian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Liberia's Charles Taylor today was
sworn in as new president of the war-ravaged country in the
capital Monrovia.
</P>
<P>
A valid report monitored here said eight African heads of
state, including Nigeria's General Sani Abacha who is also
chairman of the Economic Community of West African States and
former U.S. President Jimmy Carter, were present at Taylor's
inauguration ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of Monrovians went on a march in the streets of the
capital to celebrate the occasion, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Taylor won a landslide victory in the country's post-war
election on July 19, getting 75 percent of the valid votes.
</P>
<P>
The election, monitored by international observers, was widely
regarded as free and fair.
</P>
<P>
Analysts noted that Taylor's inauguration brought an end to
the country's seven-year bloody civil war that killed nearly
200,000 people, displaced about a million others and destroyed
the national economy.
</P>
<P>
The war began in December 1989 when Taylor launched a rebel
fight against the late President Samuel Doe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
