<DOCNO> XIE19970803.0013 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pintussevich Taped 10.90 Seconds in Women's 100m Heats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Zhanna Pintussevich of Ukraine clocked
the fastest time in the women's 100 meters second round here Saturday
at the 6th World Athletics Championships.
</P>
<P>
The little-known sprinter hit the tape first in her group with a
brilliant time of 10.90 seconds, the second fastest this year to 10.89
set by Gail Devers of the United States.
</P>
<P>
The hot favourite Marion Jones of the United States, who had beaten
the 11-second barrier five times last month, romped home first in the
third group in 10.96. The former basketball player slowed down her
pace in the final stage, and looked in hot form.
</P>
<P>
With Devers out of the 100 meters, Jones, whose best time this year
was 10.90, is well on course to win her first world title.
</P>
<P>
Merlene Ottey of Jamaica, 37, is still very powerful in the race,
winning her group in 11 seconds. She is the most dangerous threat to
Jones in the 100 meters.
</P>
<P>
The women's 100 meters final is arranged on Sunday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
