<DOCNO> XIE19970803.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-02 17:49 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israeli Troops Launch Attacks on South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Israeli troops this morning
launched attacks on suspected guerrilla positions of the
Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, in southern Lebanon,
but causing no casualties, Lebanon News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The artillery bombardments were targeted at villages near the
city of Jezzine, north of the so-called "security zone" in south
Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The area is believed to be used by the guerrillas as a base for
operations against Israeli soldiers and their militia allies, the
South Lebanon Army (SLA).
</P>
<P>
Accompanying the bombardment, Israeli warplanes carried out
reconnaissnce flights over the highlands of Iqlim al-Tuffah,
which faces the Israeli-occupied border enclave in the south,
military sources were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Three hours later, the Islamic Resistance, the military wing
of Hezbollah, began to respond to the attack by firing machine guns
and rockets at an Israeli patrol on a road in Jezzine.
</P>
<P>
The attacks between the guerrillas, and Israeli troops and the
SLA take place almost everyday since Israel established a buffer
zone of 1,100 square kilometers in 1985 in southern Lebanon to
protect northern Israel from cross-border attacks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
