<HEADLINE> Overseas Zimbabweans Launch Fund for Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean President Robert
Mugabe tonight hailed the launch of the African Resources
Investment Fund as a timely initiative that would help his
government's efforts to achieve black economic empowerment.
</P>
<P>
Mugabe made the remarks at the fund's launching gala in
Johannesburg.
</P>
<P>
Spearheaded by a Zimbabwean business group based in South
Africa, the fund aims to boost acquisition of companies in
Zimbabwe by disadvantaged blacks to correct economic imbalances
inherited at independence from Britain in 1980.
</P>
<P>
Mugabe said he applauds the efforts of the non-resident
Zimbabweans who have come up with the fund aimed at promoting
black economic empowerment.
</P>
<P>
The overseas Zimbabweans have so far raised 27.27 million U.S
dollars for the fund, which will be generated through a share
issue before the end of August.
</P>
<P>
The gala was attended by South African President Nelson
Mandela and several Zimbabwean cabinet ministers.
</P>
<P>
About four million Zimbabweans live and work in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
The fund, inaugurated last November in Johannesburg, has now
attracted Zimbabwean contributors in the United States, Britain
and Botswana. 
</P>
