<HEADLINE> Jordanian PM Blasts Israeli Measures Against </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian Prime Minister Abdul
Salam al Majali today blasted measures taken by Israel against
Palestinians after the Jerusalem bombing attack on Israelis,
saying they violated Palestinians' rights.
</P>
<P>
Majali made the remark in a statement relased upon his arrival
here on a two-day official visit, during which he is expected to
exchange views with United Arab Emirates (UAE) leaders on the
latest developments in the Mideast peace process.
</P>
<P>
"Israel should condemn itself, not another side (in the peace
process). I do not think the Palestinian National Authority is an
abettor of violence," he added.
</P>
<P>
Israeli security forces have arrested dozens of Palestinians
after the Wednesday bomb attack which killed 15 people and it also
claimed the PNA was behind the violence.
</P>
<P>
The attack has pushed the Middle East peace process to a
further retrogression. The peace process was set in deadlock
after Israel decided in February to build thousands of houses in
East Jerusalem which the Palestinians want to be the capital of a
future state.
</P>
<P>
The Jordanian prime minister said "We are regretful over the
latest matters in the Middle East peace process. We do not think
Israel could get peace without giving Palestinians legal rights."
</P>
<P>
This is the second visit by Majali to the UAE in less than two
months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
