<HEADLINE> Chiluba: Zambia's Economic Environment "Stable" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- President Frederick Chiluba said
today that Zambia's macro economic environment has stabilized
considerably.
</P>
<P>
Officially opening the 71st agricultural and commercial show
here, Chiluba said that this year's theme for the show --
"sustainable growth" -- is most appropriate as it depicts the
performance of Zambia.
</P>
<P>
He reaffirmed the government commitment to pursue policies
conducive to the promotion of local entrepreneurship.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba said the government is putting in place initiatives to
ensure the rural economy diversification succeeds.
</P>
<P>
"My government is committed to improving the quality of life
of our rural people, especially the rural farmer," he said.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba accused some traders of swindling out small scale
farmers of their produce, saying the unscrupulous traders should
be punished.
</P>
<P>
He said that farmers have not only been swindled by the
traders but have also been paid very low prices for their
produce.
</P>
<P>
The state of affairs undermines government efforts to improve
the quality of life through agriculture, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba toured the show before making the address.
</P>
<P>
A total of 270 local and foreign exhibitors are participating
in this year's show. 
</P>
</TEXT>
