<HEADLINE> Diplomatic Sanction Against Bosnia Proposed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sarajevo, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The international community High
Representative Carlos Westendorp on Saturday called for contacts
with current Bosnia's ambassadors to be suspended after its three
ethnic factions failed to meet a deadline on allocating diplomatic
posts.
</P>
<P>
"I am obliged by Sintra to propose the measures to the
international community, as from now, not to deal with ambassadors
who do not represent the country as a whole," Westendorp told a
press conference here.
</P>
<P>
During an international conference in Sintra, Portugal, two
months ago, participants set August 1 as the deadline for Bosnian
partities to reach an agreement on the diplomatic posts.
</P>
<P>
Despite mediation from Westendorp, leaders of the Bosnian
muslins, Serbs and Croats still dispute on the ethnic make-up of
diplomatic corps and diplomatic positions for each nation.
</P>
<P>
Current ambassadors in foreign countries are no longer
recognized as legitimate representatives of Bosnia until the
parties reach an agreement, Westendorp said.
</P>
<P>
The High Representative said that he has postposed until Monday
the announcement of punitive measures on issues of citizenship and
common passport, which should also be solved by Friday.
</P>
<P>
If those two issues are not solved by Monday, he might propose
the international community not recognize passports of the Bosnian
officials responsible for the failure, Westendorp said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
