<HEADLINE> Rape Cases Increase in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 2 (Xinhua) -- A cabinet minister today said
1,866 rape cases were reported in Zimbabwe since the beginning of
this year in what is increasingly becoming a menace for the
country.
</P>
<P>
Health and Child Welfare Minister Timothy Stamps said 833 or
45 percent of the cases involved abuse of juveniles, some of them
by close relatives or individuals in positions of trust.
</P>
<P>
Officially opening a one-day forum on child abuse and rape of
minors in Harare, Stamps said there is urgent need to tackle the
cause of the problem and punish those who carry out such acts.
</P>
<P>
He said on average four juveniles were raped daily in each of
the country's eight provinces.
</P>
<P>
Harare was leading with the number of reported cases ranging
between 11 and 12 per day, while Bulawayo, the country's second
largest city had an average of eight cases recorded per day.
</P>
<P>
"In the past, we didn't want to know about these things, but
we now have to face up to the risk caused by this menace because
those who abuse children do not realize the danger done to the
victim's personality," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
