<HEADLINE> Japan Beats Canada in Women's Field Hockey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Japan defeated Canada 4-2 at the
women's World Cup qualifying tournament here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Japan were one goal down in the Pool A clash after Canada's Amy
MacFarlaine scored in the 12th minute.
</P>
<P>
The exciting match contrasted the tall, leggy physiques and
fluid running of the Canadians against the squarely-built and
disciplined Japanese.
</P>
<P>
Hisayho Takahashi provided the equaliser in the 14th minute
with Sakae Morimoto putting Japan ahead after a splendid pass from
Takahashi three minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Although Agibhinn Grimes levelled for Canada on the interval,
the Japanese controlled the second half with goals from left
winger Akemi Kato and a spectacular fourth from their outstanding
player, Sachimi Iwao, who scored with a reverse sweep shot from
the edge of the circle. 
</P>
