<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1500 GMT, August 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON -- Lao Foreign Minister Somsavat Lengsavad arrived here
Sunday on a visit to Myanmar at the invitation of his Myanmar
counterpart U Ohn Gyaw.
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- A total of 66 people died in seven air crashes in
Russia in the first half of the year, the Interfax news agency
reported. The deaths were almost twice as many as in the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
ABU DHABI -- Jordanian Prime Minister Abdul Salam al Majali
Sunday ended his visit to the United Arab Emirates with a call on
Israel to give the Palestinians legal rights.
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- Kuwaiti Information Minister Sheikh Saud Nasser
Al-Sabah has underlined the need to activate multilateral
organizations to safeguard collective security in the Gulf region.
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- Foreign ministers from Luxembourg, the Netherlands
and Britain will visit the Democratic Republic of Congo on Monday
and Tuesday to promote European Union's relations with the new
African republic. 
</P>
