<HEADLINE> Li Peng Calls for Improved Relics Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nanchang, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng has
called for improving the protection of revolutionary cultural
relics and using them to inspire greater enthusiasm for
modernization construction.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to the National Revolutionary Cultural Relics
Protection Conference convened here today, the premier said relics
from past revolutionaries represent the national spirit and
reflect China's revolutionary history. Li said related relices
must be protected in order to inspire the entire nation to work
for the great cause of modernization construction.
</P>
