In a written speech delivered to the conference, State
Councillor Li Tieying called for expanded efforts to collect, sort
and research items and historic documents left over from former
generations of revolutionaries.
</P>
<P>
He also called for perfecting and effectively enforcing related
laws and regulations.
</P>
<P>
China is home to more than 300 revolutionary museums and
monuments, some 8,000 revolutionary historical sites, and over
7,000 cemeteries for revolutionary martyrs. 
