<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Most Manufacturers in Shanghai Intend to invest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shanghai, August 3 (Xinhua) -- A recent survey shows that some
40 percent of manufacturers in Shanghai, China's largest
metropolitan area, intend to invest over the next six months.
</P>
<P>
A local industrial forecasting group conducted the survey of
274 manufacturers between June 25 and July 15. Enterprises
involved in the survey generated a total 1996 output value of 144
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-nine percent of the respondents cited investment
intentions during the next six months, with the majority planning
to improve their competitive edge by investing in their own
manufacturing sector.
</P>
<P>
Fifty-one percent of respondents expressing no intention to
invest were either facing financial difficulties, unsure of good
investment opportunities, or simply lacked confidence in the
macroeconomic environment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
