<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Students from 17 universities in
China's inland areas, Hong Kong and Macao are spending two weeks
of their summer vacation in Lhasa, capital of the Tibet Autonomous
Region.
</P>
<P>
During the vacation, which started Friday, the students will
visit pastoral areas, factories, mines and cultural relics to
study the region's economic achievement and potential for future
development. The students from Hong Kong and Macao are scheduled
to have discussions with the Tibetan students on the customs and
religious practices of the Tibetan people.
</P>
<P>
Students will also discuss various approaches for introducing
Hong Kong's educational expertise to accelerate the development of
education in Tibet.
</P>
<P>
