<HEADLINE> Spain, Puerto Rico Win at Under-22 Basketball Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Spain and Puerto Rico both
captured preliminary victories on the third day of the second
world under-22 men's basketball championship in Melbourne on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Spain remained unbeaten with a 90-67 win over Argentina in
Group A, while Puerto Rico hit 16 three-pointers on the way to a
96-89 upset over European champions Lithuania in Group B.
</P>
<P>
Andre Miller and Pat Garrity scored 14 points each as the
United States crushed China 107-39 to lead Group B.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslavia took its first win at the championship after edging
New Zealand 79-76 thanks to a three pointer from Dragan Lukovski
in the dying time.
</P>
<P>
Turkey kept in medal contention with their second success in a
70-49 win over Egypt in Group A.
</P>
<P>
In Sunday's late match, Australia beat South Korea 81-61 in
Group A after leading 49-27 at half-time. 
</P>
