<HEADLINE> Thais Warned of Dengue Fever </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Dengue fever has killed 27 people
in Thailand this year and the figure is likely to rise as the
rainy season sets in, a Thai Public Health official warned on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Some 10,850 people in Thailand have contracted dengue fever so
far this year and the number is expected to reach 48,000 to 50,000
by the end of this year, according to Samrerng Yanggratoke, deputy
director-general of the Communicable Disease Control Department
under the Public Health Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The department is working on measures to curb the
mosquito-borne disease in the 20 most-affect provinces in the
country, he was quoted as saying by local newspapers.  
</P>
