<HEADLINE> Blast Injures 5 Soldiers in Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Five soldiers of the border
security force were injured in a powerful landmine blast in
Pulwama district in Indian-held south Kashmir today.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that a landmine placed on a main
road was denoted by remote control when a vehicle of the border
security force carrying soldiers were passing by. The powerful
blast rocked the area injuring five soldiers and damaging the
vehicle.
</P>
<P>
No one has claimed responsibility for the blast so far.
</P>
</TEXT>
