<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India's Inflation Registers 4.19 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The annual rate of inflation
based on wholesale price index in India touched an all-time low of
4.19 percent during the week ended July 19, Press Trust of India
(PTI) said here today.
</P>
<P>
The rate of inflation calculated on a point-to-point basis fell
by 0.24 percentage points from 4.43 percent in the previous week
to the current level of 4.19 percent. Compared to this, inflation
was at 6.01 percent in the corresponding week last year.
</P>
<P>
Since June this year, inflation has fallen by a massive 1.74
percentage points in seven weeks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
