<HEADLINE> Guangxi Speeds up Construction of Key Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region collected 7.4 billion yuan for its key projects
in the first half of this year, accounting for 41 percent of the
region's annual budget for the sector.
</P>
<P>
A series of preferential policies have been made to encourage
construction of its 50 major projects, local authorities said,
adding that 17 of them will go into operation within this year,
and construction will begin on another 12 in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The Guizhou-Liuzhou expressway has gone into operation,
track-laying work on the Nanning-Kunming railway line has been
completed, and the first generating unit of the Jingnan hydropower
station has been put into use, officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
