<HEADLINE> EU Mission to Visit Congo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Foreign ministers from
Luxembourg, the Netherlands and Britain will visit the Democratic
Republic of Congo on Monday and Tuesday to promote European
Union's relations with the new African republic.
</P>
<P>
Jacques Poos, Foreign Minister of Luxembourg which is serving
the rotating presidency of the 15-nation EU, will be joined by his
Dutch and British counterparts, Hans van Mierlo and Robin Cook, on
the trip to Kinshasa.
</P>
<P>
The three EU foreign ministers are expected to meet Congolese
President Laurent Kabila and Foreign Minister Bizima Karaha to
discuss the country's democratization process, EU humanitarian aid
and future relations between Congo and EU, according to a
Luxembourg foreign ministry press release here today.
</P>
<P>
The trip was planned on June 2 when the EU Council decided to
undertake ministerial-level contact with the new-born state.
</P>
<P>
The Democratic Republic of Congo, a central African country and
a former colony of Belgium, is rich in mineral resources,
especially non-ferrous and rare metals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
