<HEADLINE> Mahathir to Consider Meeting Soros </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad said today he would consider meeting American
financier George Soros whom he had identified as the "rogue
speculator" for manipulating currencies in Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
"Well, I will certainly consider it (meeting Soros)," Mahathir
said when asked to comment on a New Straits Times report today
that Soros, in an interview with the paper in New York, sought to
meet Mahathir.
</P>
<P>
Soros also denied his company had made speculative attacks on
several ASEAN currencies including Malaysia's ringgit.
</P>
<P>
"We'll find out what he wants to explain," Mahathir said after
seeing off his Pakistani counterpart Nawaz Sharif at the Kuala
Lumpur International Airport.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said earlier that his government had definite evidence
that the pressure on the ringgit and other ASEAN currencies was
caused by Soros.
</P>
<P>
According to the newspaper report, Soros said he would like to
meet Mahathir, possibly in November when he addresses the
International Monetary Fund-World Bank meeting in Hong Kong, to
discuss in a public forum their differences.
</P>
<P>
However, Soros made it clear that he had no desire to do battle
with Mahathir despite their differences, the report said.
</P>
</TEXT>
