<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Energy Regulation Board Set up in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Zambia has set up an Energy
Regulation Board (ERB) to ensure the smooth and orderly operation
of the energy setor of the country, Sunday Times of Zambia
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The board was launched here Saturday by Energy and Water
Development Minister Suresh Desai.
</P>
<P>
When launching the board, Desai said that the board is
entitled to a grant from the government and that this has already
been catered for by a provision of 106 million kwacha (about
81,500 U.S Dollars) in the 1997 budget.
</P>
<P>
He said that he expected the board headed by Raphael
Salasini,the Chairman and Director of the private sector, to
address the major concerns facing the energy sector related to
shortage, handling, transportation and sale of petroleum
products.
</P>
<P>
"It is also my expectation that the board will be instrumental
in the strict enforcement of housekeeping standards in the energy
sector, and ensuring that only credible investors were allowed to
participate in this vitally important sector," he said.
</P>
<P>
The board will look at the impact of energy on the environment
and will work closely with the Environmental Council of Zambia to
ensure environmental standards are strictly adhered to in the
sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
