<DOCNO> XIE19970803.0112 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over 90,000 Zimbabwean Workers Lose Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Over 90,000 Zimbabwean workers
have lost their jobs in the construction industry due to the lull
in property development when a number of construction companies
have gone under, the Sunday Mail reported today.
</P>
<P>
The industry, which has not yet recovered from the recession a
couple of years ago, was dealt a further blow by the recent
action which resulted in a loss of hundreds of man hours and
millions of dollars.
</P>
<P>
In most of the urban centers, construction work has trickled
down to a minimum with most of the major work started some time
ago currently being done.
</P>
<P>
Oliver Chidawu, one of the leading contractors in civil and
electrical engineering who is also former President of the
Zimbabwe Building Contractors' Association, said that in general
the industry was down.
</P>
<P>
The construction industry used to employ over 120,000 workers,
Chidawu said, adding "We estimate that only about 28,000 are
employed right now". 
</P>
</TEXT>
