<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South African Quka Takes WBU Bantamweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROMA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Patrick Quka of South Africa knocked
down Italy's Gianmaria Petriccioli twice Saturday to win the
bantaweight title fight of the World Boxing Union at San Mango
D'Aquino, Italy.
</P>
<P>
The South African's one-two punch at the beginning of the
next-to-last round ensured his win. American referee Tony Orlando
stopped the contest after one minute, 25 seconds into the 11th
round as the punch-drunk Italian was uncapable to continue the
bout after suffering two knockdowns.
</P>
<P>
The 27-year-old Italian, appearently lacked of technique and
preciseness, was decked for the first time in the ninth round, and
was on the canvas a few seconds later.
</P>
<P>
Quka, 24, lifted his record to 20 wins and one loss after he
captured the vacant WBU title while Petriccioli's record dropped
to 10-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
