<HEADLINE> Pivotals Remain Firm on BSE Last Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Pivotals remained firm on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market last week mainly due to brisk
buying support by foreign institutional investors coupled with
local speculative buying.
</P>
<P>
The BSE sensitive index recovered from 4,163.53 to 4,356.55
before finishing at 4,348.32 with sizable gain of 158.51 points
compared to the previous week level of 4,189.81. The national
index also gained 68.80 points to 1,891.90 as against the previous
level of 1,823.10.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said the trading sentiment turned for the better mainly
due to aggressive buying by foreign institutional investors
coupled with fresh interest shown by speculators following the
somewhat improved political situation in the country. The uptrend
was also on account of encouraging first quarter performance
announced by major companies in the country.  
</P>
