<HEADLINE> Solidarity Meeting in Cuba Condemns U.S. Imperialism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- A meeting of about 1,000 young
people from around the world opened here today to show solidarity
with Cuba in resisting the U.S. imperialism.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, with its theme as the Solidarity With Cuba Against
the United States Trade Embargo, is part of the 14th World Youth
Festival and Conference of Youth and Students.
</P>
<P>
Participants blasted the United States for its 30 years of
embargo against Cuba, 1989 invasion of Panama, "colonialization"
of Puerto Rico and bombing of Iraq during the Gulf War.
</P>
<P>
Puerto Rico independence movement leader Rafael Miranda told
the audience that Puerto Rico was used by the United States to
test napalm bombs and radiation devices.
</P>
<P>
Lucius Walker, a U.S. national representing the Pastors for
Peace group, called for continued resistance to the Torricelli and
Helms-Burton bills enacted by the United States to punish Cuba.
</P>
