<HEADLINE> Pakistan PM Ends Visit to Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif left here today for home after a four-day visit to
Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Sharif and his Malaysian counterpart Mahathir
Mohamad met for talks and agreed that bilateral cooperation should
be further expanded in the fields of science and technology,
education and defense.
</P>
<P>
The two countries signed a memorandum of understanding on
defense cooperation, covering training of officers and possible
cooperation in the defense industry. Defense is a new area of
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
In the field of education, Malaysia hoped that Pakistan would
provide places at its institutions of higher learning to Malaysian
students to pursue medicine, pharmacy and dentistry.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Mahathir and Sharif also witnessed the
signing of an agreement between Malaysia's Inno-Enhance Private
Limited, Pakistan's Punjab provincial government and the Punjab
Industrial Board for the setting up of an export-processing zone
in Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia said the two countries could cooperate in seeking
opportunities in third countries especially in the
newly-independent central Asian republics where there are market
potentials.
</P>
<P>
On regional issues, Malaysia welcomed Pakistan's new status as
a sectoral dialogue partner of ASEAN to further promote trade ties
between ASEAN and the South Asian country.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan expressed its interest in joining the Asia-Pacific
Economic Cooperation (APEC) forum and the Asia-Europe Meeting
(ASEM), and sought support from Malaysia in this regard. Malaysia
said Pakistan's requests for membership should be discussed with
other members of the two bodies.
</P>
<P>
On Kashmir, Malaysia lauded the initiative by Pakistan and
India to hold talks to solve the problem.
</P>
<P>
On Afghanistan, both Malaysia and Pakistan expressed the hope
that political stability would return to the war-torn country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
