<HEADLINE> Chinese PLA Chief of General Staff Leaves for US, Finland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- General Fu Quanyou, member of
China's Central Military Commission and chief of the General Staff
of the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA), left here this
morning for an official visit to the United States and Finland.
</P>
<P>
Fu was invited by John Shalikashvili, chairman of the US Joint
Chiefs of Staff, and Gustav Hagglund, commander-in-chief of the
Finnish National Defense Forces.
</P>
<P>
Fu's party includes Lieutenant General Xu Zhenzhong,
deputy-commander of the PLA Navy, Lieutenant General Lu Denghua,
deputy commander of the Nanjing Military Area Command and
commander of the air force of the military area command, and
Lieutenant General Chen Xitao, chief of the Staff of the Beijing
Military Area Command.
</P>
<P>
Fu's visits constitute an important component part of the
high-level exchanges of armed forces between China and the US and
between China and Finland. During the trips, Fu is expected to
confer with John Shalikashvili and Gustav Hagglund respectively on
bilateral ties, relations between their armed forces and regional
security of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Fu will meet with ranking government officials and
other military leaders of the two countries and visit units of the
three services and military academies of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
These activities will facilitate increasing mutual
understanding and trust and help expand bilateral ties between
China and the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Among those seeing Fu and his party off at the airport were
Lieutenant General Xiong Guangkai, deputy chief of the PLA General
Staff, as well as embassy officials of the two countries in
Beijing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
