<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Foreign Trade Joint Venture Set up in Shanghai's Pudong Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 3 (Xinhua) -- A third foreign trade joint
venture will be set up in Shanghai's Pudong New Area with the
approval of the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation
(MOFTEC), it was announced recently.
</P>
<P>
The new foreign trade company will be jointly funded by the
China National Technical Import and Export Corporation (CNTIEC)
and Sun Kyong Ltd. of the Republic of Korea (ROK).
</P>
<P>
An executive of the new company said it has a registered
capital of 100 million yuan (12 million US dollars). CNTIEC will
bear 51 percent of the total investment and the ROK company will
cover the rest.
</P>
<P>
The 45-year-old CNTIEC has concluded some 3,200 import and
export deals, with the business volume climbing to more than 65
billion U.S. dollars. It ranks first among enterprises engaged in
electro-mechanical imports and exports in China.
</P>
<P>
So far, three foreign trade joint ventures have registered to
build their headquarters in Pudong, the designated pilot of
China's reform and opening-up drive which benefits from a number
of preferential policies.
</P>
<P>
The two other joint ventures are the Dongling Trading
Corporation founded by two local companies of Shanghai, the
Mitsubishi Corp. of Japan and another company in the United
States, and Lansheng-Daewoo Co. Ltd., established by Shanghai
Lansheng Group and Daewoo Corp of ROK.
</P>
<P>
Local sources say that more local companies in Shanghai have
applied to establish foreign trade joint ventures.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
