<HEADLINE> Honduras Wins Central-American Volleyball Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANAMA CITY, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Honduras overpowered
Guatemala to win the title of the ninth Central American men's
volleyball championship here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Honduras lost the first set 15-17 for their poor defence. But
they soon controlled the play to win 16-14, 15-12, 15-4 in a roll.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rica stormed a 3-2 come-back victory of 10-15, 3-15,
15-7, 15-8, 17-15 over defending champion Banama, which captured
the last three titles in a roll, to finish the third place in the
six-nation championship which started on July 27. 
</P>
