<HEADLINE> Moderate Economic Growth Recorded in Guangxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Intensive reform fueled steady
economic growth in south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region
in the first half of the year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show the region's gross domestic product jumped 8.8
percent from the previous year to end at 85.9 billion yuan (10.7
billion US dollars), "China Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi's agricultural sector developed steadily, too, and the
trend is likely to continue. The autonomous regional government
plans to increase spending on agricultural infrastructure by 24
percent to 120 million yuan (14.5 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Its industrial output value for the first six months hit 107
billion yuan (12.89 billion US dollars), up 9.8 percent from the
1996 period.
</P>
<P>
The revenue of Guangxi rose steadily, with the 6.28 billion
yuan (75.7 million US dollars) recorded in the first six months
representing a 14.1 percent rise from the 1996 period.
</P>
<P>
Outstanding deposits for the region's financial institutions
approached 147.2 billion yuan (17.7 billion US dollars) by the end
of June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
