<HEADLINE> Train Derailment Injures Four in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Four people, including a child aged
around eight, were injured when a passenger train derailed today
in a small station near Rome.
</P>
<P>
None of the injured, all on the train travelling from Reggio
Calabria in southern Italy to Turin in the north, were in serious
conditions, hospital sources said.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place at 3:30 a.m. local time, and the first
car of the 20-carriage passenger train hit a freight train sitting
on parallel tracks at the Casilina Station.
</P>
<P>
Eleven other cars hit a high-voltage power cable.
</P>
<P>
However, aside from the four injured, the 200 other passengers
on the derailed train were able to continue their journey on other
trains, reports quoted Italy's railway company as saying.
</P>
<P>
The authorities said that an inquiry was underway to determine
the cause of the accident.
</P>
<P>
The derailment delayed train schedules around the capital by
five hours, at the height of the holiday season when millions of
Italians leave on vacation and foreign tourists arrive. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
