<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guilin to Hold Tourism Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The Sixth Guilin Mountain and
River Tourism Festival is expected to be held from October 30 to
November 2 in this city of south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region. Meanwhile, the Guilin-Guangxi Trade Talks will take place.
</P>
<P>
The two events are sponsored by the Guilin city government, a
Hong Kong tourism organization, and the China Tourism News.
</P>
<P>
Sources estimate a total of 1,400 guests from both overseas and
elsewhere in China, as well as 200,000 local residents will attend
the festival.
</P>
<P>
On October 31, the first Guilin Tourism Products Exhibition
will bring in nearly 1,000 manufacturers of arts and crafts and
sales people from the industry. The event is aimed at promoting
exchanges and cooperation between Guilin and other areas in the
sectors of tourism, trade, culture, and science and technology.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
