<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pilot Flower-Growing Base Set up in Northeast China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 3 (Xinhua) -- A 30-million-yuan flower-growing
base was set up recently in Shenyang, the capital of northeast
China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The pilot research center, which covers a 14 ha. of land,
boasts more than 20,000 sq m of state-of-the-art greenhouses with
equipment imported from Holland.
</P>
<P>
It also has 640 sq m of research and cultivating facilities,
and is expected to become a leading site in Liaoning for its work.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning now has more than 1,300 ha. of planted flowers. It can
grow 30 million fresh flowers a year, bringing the local total
fresh flower income to more than 200 million yuan (24 million US
dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
